# Quant Terminal UI Rules — Profile Refactor Prompt (Cursor)

Use this prompt when refactoring `src/components/Profile.tsx` (and only minimal wiring in `src/App.tsx` if needed).

## Role
Senior React/TypeScript + Tailwind UI Engineer.

## Goal
Refactor the **Profile** page so it matches the Oddsflow **“Quant Terminal”** design language: high-contrast, black/gold material, data-dense, stable numeric layout.

## Hard Rules (must follow)
- **Background**: must be `#0A0A0A`.
- **Cards**: must use `bg-[#161616] border border-white/5 rounded-xl`.
- **Gold**: must be `#FFD700` (no other gold variants).
- **VIP badge**: must be `border border-[#4ADE80]/30 text-[#4ADE80] bg-transparent`.
- **Labels**: must be `text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500`.
- **Numbers / currency / IDs**: must use **monospace + tabular**: `font-mono tabular-nums`.
- **Buttons**: must be `rounded-xl`, same height across the page, include `hover:brightness-110 transition`.
- **Constraints**:
  - Do **NOT** delete any existing business logic.
  - Only refactor layout/structure/styling.
  - Keep existing callbacks/props working.

## Layout Requirements

### 1) Header Card
- One top card with account info.
- Username should have subtle gold glow (text-shadow or drop-shadow).
- VIP expiry must show **“Expires in X Days”** (calculate from `vip_end_time`).
- De-emphasize non-core text; emphasize username + balance.

### 2) Wallet Row (inside header card)
- Use `flex justify-between items-center`.
- Left: label **Wallet Balance** + value in `#FFD700` (slightly smaller than previous, `tracking-tight`, subtle gold shadow).
- Right: CTA button **OPEN** in `#FFD700`, black text, `font-black`, same height as VIP pill.

### 3) Stats Grid
- 3 columns with dividers: `border-r border-white/10`.
- Each cell: label (spec above) + large value (white, monospace).

### 4) Shortcuts
- Render from an array: `{ icon, label, onClick }`.
- Each row has `hover:scale-105 transition-transform` and includes a chevron-right at the end.

## Wiring
- Keep Support accessible from Profile.
- If `watchlistCount` exists in App state, pass it into Profile and display it.

